Business' Survey

Pictures from GRAND OPENING

Our Mission:

To educate and train low income individuals in the Tri-Cities, which includes but will not be limited to Johnson City, Kingsport, and Bristol, Tennessee for general employment. To network and telemarket with residents to address their social needs.

Our Vision:

Providing low income individuals with a sense of self, to empower them with confidence through education and training, while obtaining valuable skills to obtain gainful employment within their community. Through ASPET Inc. programs to provide the special and social needs of the community for residents and businesses.

Our Students:

Low income community residents in need of academic education and on the job training (OJT). We will also accept students in the program who are on Probation and/or Parole, House Arrest, and Veterans and homeless. However no sex and violent offenders will be permitted into the program.
   Splash of Panache. Powered by Star Technology Group.
Send all inquiries to info@SplashofPanache.org. Direct technical questions or comments to: webmaster@StarTechnologyGroup.com.
